# Native build artifacts.
#
# The compiled libraries (libtlsn_mobile.{so,a}, TlsnMobile.xcframework)
# are large binaries — regenerated by build-ios.sh / build-android.sh and
# kept out of git. The uniffi-generated Kotlin/Swift bindings, however,
# are committed: they are small text files, deterministic from the Rust
# source, and the hand-written bridge can't compile without them. CI
# environments (EAS in particular) reliably get them from git this way,
# independent of whichever .easignore / packaging rules apply.

# iOS — binary only; tlsn_mobile.swift IS tracked.
ios/TlsnMobile.xcframework/
ios/lib/
ios/include/

# Android — binary only; uniffi/ binding IS tracked.
android/src/main/jniLibs/
